name: NAT (Natural seed Aging Treatment)
scoring: The germination ratio was scored after 7 days and corrected with the control germination ratio.
growth_conditions: Seeds were aged for 18 months of dry-storage at ambient laboratory conditions (20-25 ºC, 40-60% RH). Chlorine gas sterilization, 7 days of seed vernalization and MS media sowing was used for 269 ecotypes to ensure same treatment and growing conditions.
eo_definition: "A physical plant treatment (EO:0007316) involving an exposure to varying degree of temperature, which may depend on regional environment." [GR:pj]
uo_definition: "A dimensionless unit which denotes an amount or magnitude of one quantity relative to another." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

name: EPPO (Elevated Partial Pressure of Oxygen seed-aging treatment)
scoring: The germination ratio was scored after 7 days and corrected with the control germination ratio.
growth_conditions: Seeds were artificially aged in a 5 bar of oxygen chamber for 5 months with a 40% of relative humidity and ambient temperature (20-25 ºC). Chlorine gas sterilization, 7 days of seed vernalization and MS media sowing was used for 267 ecotypes to ensure same treatment and growing conditions.
eo_definition: "A chemical stress treatment (EO:0001036) involving use of oxidative stress-inducing chemicals." [PO:cooperl]
uo_definition: "A dimensionless unit which denotes an amount or magnitude of one quantity relative to another." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

name: AAT (Accelerated seed Aging Treatment)
scoring: The germination ratio was scored after 7 days and corrected with the control germination ratio.
growth_conditions: Imbedded seeds were artificially aged at 39ºC for 48h. Chlorine gas sterilization, 7 days of seed vernalization (both prior to the aging treatment) and MS media sowing was used for 269 ecotypes to ensure same treatment and growing conditions.
eo_definition: "The treatment involving an exposure to above optimal water temperature, which may depend on the study type or the regional environment." [GR:pj]
uo_definition: "A dimensionless unit which denotes an amount or magnitude of one quantity relative to another." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]

name: CDT (Controlled seed Deterioration Treatment)
scoring: The germination ratio was scored after 7 days and corrected with the control germination ratio.
growth_conditions: Seeds were artificially aged at 38ºC in 75% relative-humidity chamber for 14 days. Chlorine gas sterilization, 7 days of seed vernalization and MS media sowing was used for 267 ecotypes to ensure same treatment and growing conditions.
eo_definition: "The treatment involving an exposure to above optimal air temperature, which may depend on the study type or the regional environment." [GR:pj]
uo_definition: "A dimensionless unit which denotes an amount or magnitude of one quantity relative to another." [Wikipedia:Wikipedia]
